scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series primarily comprises surveys, statistical notes, drafts, memoranda, proposals, manuscripts, correspondence, publications, and reports Wilkinson collected for her research. Topics include Diagnosing the Therapist: Race and Gender in Clinical Decision Making; Forgotten Pioneers Series research and work on early African Americans' presence in physics, medicine, and other specific areas; race and gender consciousness; ethnicity; barbershops; and African American heritage, women and feminization, children and families, businesses, and university faculty. There is an electronic copy of the 1893 Lexington City Directory (dated October 26, 1993) in WordPerfect format on disk 01.
